Defendant Michael L Bell in court with attorney M. Elizabeth Weathers.  Lindsey Hirt appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea as to count 1 and 2. Count 3 is dismissed and read-in. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

60 DAYS Jail on each count, consecutive to each other, 1 day credit

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*No contact with:  any victim or the Target stores
*No violent contact with any family member
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done. 
*Mental Heath evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DRGOD $10.00 each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);
